58// TODO(philipel): Change kPacketBufferStartSize back to 32 in M63 see:
59// crbug.com/752886
60constexpr int kPacketBufferStartSize = 512;
61constexpr int kPacketBufferMaxSize = 2048;
62
63int PacketBufferMaxSize() {
64 // The group here must be a positive power of 2, in which case that is used as
65 // size. All other values shall result in the default value being used.
66 const std::string group_name =
67 webrtc::field_trial::FindFullName("WebRTC-PacketBufferMaxSize");
68 int packet_buffer_max_size = kPacketBufferMaxSize;
69 if (!group_name.empty() &&
70 (sscanf(group_name.c_str(), "%d", &packet_buffer_max_size) != 1 ||
71 packet_buffer_max_size <= 0 ||
72 // Verify that the number is a positive power of 2.
73 (packet_buffer_max_size & (packet_buffer_max_size - 1)) != 0)) {
74 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Invalid packet buffer max size: " << group_name;
75 packet_buffer_max_size = kPacketBufferMaxSize;
76 }
77 return packet_buffer_max_size;
78}

80std::unique_ptr<RtpRtcp> CreateRtpRtcpModule(
81 Clock* clock,
82 ReceiveStatistics* receive_statistics,
83 Transport* outgoing_transport,
84 RtcpRttStats* rtt_stats,
85 RtcpPacketTypeCounterObserver* rtcp_packet_type_counter_observer,
86 RtcpCnameCallback* rtcp_cname_callback,
87 bool non_sender_rtt_measurement,
88 uint32_t local_ssrc) {
89 RtpRtcpInterface::Configuration configuration;
90 configuration.clock = clock;
91 configuration.audio = false;
92 configuration.receiver_only = true;
93 configuration.receive_statistics = receive_statistics;
94 configuration.outgoing_transport = outgoing_transport;
95 configuration.rtt_stats = rtt_stats;
96 configuration.rtcp_packet_type_counter_observer =
97 rtcp_packet_type_counter_observer;
98 configuration.rtcp_cname_callback = rtcp_cname_callback;
99 configuration.local_media_ssrc = local_ssrc;
100 configuration.non_sender_rtt_measurement = non_sender_rtt_measurement;
101
102 std::unique_ptr<RtpRtcp> rtp_rtcp = RtpRtcp::DEPRECATED_Create(configuration);
103 rtp_rtcp->SetRTCPStatus(RtcpMode::kCompound);
104
105 return rtp_rtcp;
106}

112RtpVideoStreamReceiver::RtcpFeedbackBuffer::RtcpFeedbackBuffer(
113 KeyFrameRequestSender* key_frame_request_sender,
114 NackSender* nack_sender,
115 LossNotificationSender* loss_notification_sender)
116 : key_frame_request_sender_(key_frame_request_sender),
117 nack_sender_(nack_sender),
118 loss_notification_sender_(loss_notification_sender),
119 request_key_frame_(false) {
120 RTC_DCHECK(key_frame_request_sender_);
121 RTC_DCHECK(nack_sender_);
122 RTC_DCHECK(loss_notification_sender_);
123}
124
125void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::RtcpFeedbackBuffer::RequestKeyFrame() {
126 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
127 request_key_frame_ = true;
128}
129
130void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::RtcpFeedbackBuffer::SendNack(
131 const std::vector<uint16_t>& sequence_numbers,
132 bool buffering_allowed) {
133 RTC_DCHECK(!sequence_numbers.empty());
134 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
135 nack_sequence_numbers_.insert(nack_sequence_numbers_.end(),
136 sequence_numbers.cbegin(),
137 sequence_numbers.cend());
138 if (!buffering_allowed) {
139 // Note that while *buffering* is not allowed, *batching* is, meaning that
140 // previously buffered messages may be sent along with the current message.
141 SendRtcpFeedback(ConsumeRtcpFeedbackLocked());
142 }
143}
144
145void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::RtcpFeedbackBuffer::SendLossNotification(
146 uint16_t last_decoded_seq_num,
147 uint16_t last_received_seq_num,
148 bool decodability_flag,
149 bool buffering_allowed) {
150 RTC_DCHECK(buffering_allowed);
151 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
152 RTC_DCHECK(!lntf_state_)
153 << "SendLossNotification() called twice in a row with no call to "
154 "SendBufferedRtcpFeedback() in between.";
155 lntf_state_ = absl::make_optional<LossNotificationState>(
156 last_decoded_seq_num, last_received_seq_num, decodability_flag);
157}
158
159void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::RtcpFeedbackBuffer::SendBufferedRtcpFeedback() {
160 SendRtcpFeedback(ConsumeRtcpFeedback());
161}
162
163RtpVideoStreamReceiver::RtcpFeedbackBuffer::ConsumedRtcpFeedback
164RtpVideoStreamReceiver::RtcpFeedbackBuffer::ConsumeRtcpFeedback() {
165 MutexLock lock(&mutex_);
166 return ConsumeRtcpFeedbackLocked();
167}
168
169RtpVideoStreamReceiver::RtcpFeedbackBuffer::ConsumedRtcpFeedback
170RtpVideoStreamReceiver::RtcpFeedbackBuffer::ConsumeRtcpFeedbackLocked() {
171 ConsumedRtcpFeedback feedback;
172 std::swap(feedback.request_key_frame, request_key_frame_);
173 std::swap(feedback.nack_sequence_numbers, nack_sequence_numbers_);
174 std::swap(feedback.lntf_state, lntf_state_);
175 return feedback;
176}
177
178void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::RtcpFeedbackBuffer::SendRtcpFeedback(
179 ConsumedRtcpFeedback feedback) {
180 if (feedback.lntf_state) {
181 // If either a NACK or a key frame request is sent, we should buffer
182 // the LNTF and wait for them (NACK or key frame request) to trigger
183 // the compound feedback message.
184 // Otherwise, the LNTF should be sent out immediately.
185 const bool buffering_allowed =
186 feedback.request_key_frame || !feedback.nack_sequence_numbers.empty();
187
188 loss_notification_sender_->SendLossNotification(
189 feedback.lntf_state->last_decoded_seq_num,
190 feedback.lntf_state->last_received_seq_num,
191 feedback.lntf_state->decodability_flag, buffering_allowed);
192 }
193
194 if (feedback.request_key_frame) {
195 key_frame_request_sender_->RequestKeyFrame();
196 } else if (!feedback.nack_sequence_numbers.empty()) {
197 nack_sender_->SendNack(feedback.nack_sequence_numbers, true);
198 }
199}

231RtpVideoStreamReceiver::RtpVideoStreamReceiver(
232 Clock* clock,
233 Transport* transport,
234 RtcpRttStats* rtt_stats,
235 PacketRouter* packet_router,
236 const VideoReceiveStream::Config* config,
237 ReceiveStatistics* rtp_receive_statistics,
238 RtcpPacketTypeCounterObserver* rtcp_packet_type_counter_observer,
239 RtcpCnameCallback* rtcp_cname_callback,
240 ProcessThread* process_thread,
241 NackSender* nack_sender,
242 KeyFrameRequestSender* keyframe_request_sender,
243 OnCompleteFrameCallback* complete_frame_callback,
244 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameDecryptorInterface> frame_decryptor,
245 rtc::scoped_refptr<FrameTransformerInterface> frame_transformer)
246 : clock_(clock),
247 config_(*config),
248 packet_router_(packet_router),
249 process_thread_(process_thread),
250 ntp_estimator_(clock),
251 rtp_header_extensions_(config_.rtp.extensions),
252 forced_playout_delay_max_ms_("max_ms", absl::nullopt),
253 forced_playout_delay_min_ms_("min_ms", absl::nullopt),
254 rtp_receive_statistics_(rtp_receive_statistics),
255 ulpfec_receiver_(UlpfecReceiver::Create(config->rtp.remote_ssrc,
256 this,
257 config->rtp.extensions)),
258 receiving_(false),
259 last_packet_log_ms_(-1),
260 rtp_rtcp_(CreateRtpRtcpModule(
261 clock,
262 rtp_receive_statistics_,
263 transport,
264 rtt_stats,
265 rtcp_packet_type_counter_observer,
266 rtcp_cname_callback,
267 config_.rtp.rtcp_xr.receiver_reference_time_report,
268 config_.rtp.local_ssrc)),
269 complete_frame_callback_(complete_frame_callback),
270 keyframe_request_sender_(keyframe_request_sender),
271 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10336): Let |rtcp_feedback_buffer_| communicate
272 // directly with |rtp_rtcp_|.
273 rtcp_feedback_buffer_(this, nack_sender, this),
274 packet_buffer_(kPacketBufferStartSize, PacketBufferMaxSize()),
275 has_received_frame_(false),
276 frames_decryptable_(false),
277 absolute_capture_time_receiver_(clock) {
278 constexpr bool remb_candidate = true;
279 if (packet_router_)
280 packet_router_->AddReceiveRtpModule(rtp_rtcp_.get(), remb_candidate);
281
282 RTC_DCHECK(config_.rtp.rtcp_mode != RtcpMode::kOff)
283 << "A stream should not be configured with RTCP disabled. This value is "
284 "reserved for internal usage.";
285 // TODO(pbos): What's an appropriate local_ssrc for receive-only streams?
286 RTC_DCHECK(config_.rtp.local_ssrc != 0);
287 RTC_DCHECK(config_.rtp.remote_ssrc != config_.rtp.local_ssrc);
288
289 rtp_rtcp_->SetRTCPStatus(config_.rtp.rtcp_mode);
290 rtp_rtcp_->SetRemoteSSRC(config_.rtp.remote_ssrc);
291
292 static const int kMaxPacketAgeToNack = 450;
293 const int max_reordering_threshold = (config_.rtp.nack.rtp_history_ms > 0)
294 ? kMaxPacketAgeToNack
295 : kDefaultMaxReorderingThreshold;
296 rtp_receive_statistics_->SetMaxReorderingThreshold(config_.rtp.remote_ssrc,
297 max_reordering_threshold);
298 // TODO(nisse): For historic reasons, we applied the above
299 // max_reordering_threshold also for RTX stats, which makes little sense since
300 // we don't NACK rtx packets. Consider deleting the below block, and rely on
301 // the default threshold.
302 if (config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc) {
303 rtp_receive_statistics_->SetMaxReorderingThreshold(
304 config_.rtp.rtx_ssrc, max_reordering_threshold);
305 }
306 ParseFieldTrial(
307 {&forced_playout_delay_max_ms_, &forced_playout_delay_min_ms_},
308 field_trial::FindFullName("WebRTC-ForcePlayoutDelay"));
309
310 process_thread_->RegisterModule(rtp_rtcp_.get(), RTC_FROM_HERE);
311
312 if (config_.rtp.lntf.enabled) {
313 loss_notification_controller_ =
314 std::make_unique<LossNotificationController>(&rtcp_feedback_buffer_,
315 &rtcp_feedback_buffer_);
316 }
317
318 if (config_.rtp.nack.rtp_history_ms != 0) {
319 nack_module_ = std::make_unique<DEPRECATED_NackModule>(
320 clock_, &rtcp_feedback_buffer_, &rtcp_feedback_buffer_);
321 process_thread_->RegisterModule(nack_module_.get(), RTC_FROM_HERE);
322 }
323
324 reference_finder_ = std::make_unique<RtpFrameReferenceFinder>(this);
325
326 // Only construct the encrypted receiver if frame encryption is enabled.
327 if (config_.crypto_options.sframe.require_frame_encryption) {
328 buffered_frame_decryptor_ =
329 std::make_unique<BufferedFrameDecryptor>(this, this);
330 if (frame_decryptor != nullptr) {
331 buffered_frame_decryptor_->SetFrameDecryptor(std::move(frame_decryptor));
332 }
333 }
334
335 if (frame_transformer) {
336 frame_transformer_delegate_ =
337 rtc::make_ref_counted<RtpVideoStreamReceiverFrameTransformerDelegate>(
338 this, std::move(frame_transformer), rtc::Thread::Current(),
339 config_.rtp.remote_ssrc);
340 frame_transformer_delegate_->Init();
341 }
342}
343
344RtpVideoStreamReceiver::~RtpVideoStreamReceiver() {
345 RTC_DCHECK(secondary_sinks_.empty());
346
347 if (nack_module_) {
348 process_thread_->DeRegisterModule(nack_module_.get());
349 }
350
351 process_thread_->DeRegisterModule(rtp_rtcp_.get());
352
353 if (packet_router_)
354 packet_router_->RemoveReceiveRtpModule(rtp_rtcp_.get());
355 UpdateHistograms();
356 if (frame_transformer_delegate_)
357 frame_transformer_delegate_->Reset();
358}

360void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::AddReceiveCodec(
361 uint8_t payload_type,
362 const VideoCodec& video_codec,
363 const std::map<std::string, std::string>& codec_params,
364 bool raw_payload) {
365 if (codec_params.count(cricket::kH264FmtpSpsPpsIdrInKeyframe) ||
366 field_trial::IsEnabled("WebRTC-SpsPpsIdrIsH264Keyframe")) {
367 MutexLock lock(&packet_buffer_lock_);
368 packet_buffer_.ForceSpsPpsIdrIsH264Keyframe();
369 }
370 payload_type_map_.emplace(
371 payload_type, raw_payload
372 ? std::make_unique<VideoRtpDepacketizerRaw>()
373 : CreateVideoRtpDepacketizer(video_codec.codecType));
374 pt_codec_params_.emplace(payload_type, codec_params);
375}

377absl::optional<Syncable::Info> RtpVideoStreamReceiver::GetSyncInfo() const {
378 Syncable::Info info;
379 if (rtp_rtcp_->RemoteNTP(&info.capture_time_ntp_secs,
380 &info.capture_time_ntp_frac,
381 /*rtcp_arrival_time_secs=*/nullptr,
382 /*rtcp_arrival_time_frac=*/nullptr,
383 &info.capture_time_source_clock) != 0) {
384 return absl::nullopt;
385 }
386 {
387 MutexLock lock(&sync_info_lock_);
388 if (!last_received_rtp_timestamp_ || !last_received_rtp_system_time_) {
389 return absl::nullopt;
390 }
391 info.latest_received_capture_timestamp = *last_received_rtp_timestamp_;
392 info.latest_receive_time_ms = last_received_rtp_system_time_->ms();
393 }
394
395 // Leaves info.current_delay_ms uninitialized.
396 return info;
397}

399RtpVideoStreamReceiver::ParseGenericDependenciesResult
400RtpVideoStreamReceiver::ParseGenericDependenciesExtension(
401 const RtpPacketReceived& rtp_packet,
402 RTPVideoHeader* video_header) {
403 if (rtp_packet.HasExtension<RtpDependencyDescriptorExtension>()) {
404 webrtc::DependencyDescriptor dependency_descriptor;
405 if (!rtp_packet.GetExtension<RtpDependencyDescriptorExtension>(
406 video_structure_.get(), &dependency_descriptor)) {
407 // Descriptor is there, but failed to parse. Either it is invalid,
408 // or too old packet (after relevant video_structure_ changed),
409 // or too new packet (before relevant video_structure_ arrived).
410 // Drop such packet to be on the safe side.
411 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10342): Stash too new packet.
412 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "ssrc: " << rtp_packet.Ssrc()
413 << " Failed to parse dependency descriptor.";
414 return kDropPacket;
415 }
416 if (dependency_descriptor.attached_structure != nullptr &&
417 !dependency_descriptor.first_packet_in_frame) {
418 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "ssrc: " << rtp_packet.Ssrc()
419 << "Invalid dependency descriptor: structure "
420 "attached to non first packet of a frame.";
421 return kDropPacket;
422 }
423 video_header->is_first_packet_in_frame =
424 dependency_descriptor.first_packet_in_frame;
425 video_header->is_last_packet_in_frame =
426 dependency_descriptor.last_packet_in_frame;
427
428 int64_t frame_id =
429 frame_id_unwrapper_.Unwrap(dependency_descriptor.frame_number);
430 auto& generic_descriptor_info = video_header->generic.emplace();
431 generic_descriptor_info.frame_id = frame_id;
432 generic_descriptor_info.spatial_index =
433 dependency_descriptor.frame_dependencies.spatial_id;
434 generic_descriptor_info.temporal_index =
435 dependency_descriptor.frame_dependencies.temporal_id;
436 for (int fdiff : dependency_descriptor.frame_dependencies.frame_diffs) {
437 generic_descriptor_info.dependencies.push_back(frame_id - fdiff);
438 }
439 generic_descriptor_info.decode_target_indications =
440 dependency_descriptor.frame_dependencies.decode_target_indications;
441 if (dependency_descriptor.resolution) {
442 video_header->width = dependency_descriptor.resolution->Width();
443 video_header->height = dependency_descriptor.resolution->Height();
444 }
445
446 // FrameDependencyStructure is sent in dependency descriptor of the first
447 // packet of a key frame and required for parsed dependency descriptor in
448 // all the following packets until next key frame.
449 // Save it if there is a (potentially) new structure.
450 if (dependency_descriptor.attached_structure) {
451 RTC_DCHECK(dependency_descriptor.first_packet_in_frame);
452 if (video_structure_frame_id_ > frame_id) {
453 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
454 << "Arrived key frame with id " << frame_id << " and structure id "
455 << dependency_descriptor.attached_structure->structure_id
456 << " is older than the latest received key frame with id "
457 << *video_structure_frame_id_ << " and structure id "
458 << video_structure_->structure_id;
459 return kDropPacket;
460 }
461 video_structure_ = std::move(dependency_descriptor.attached_structure);
462 video_structure_frame_id_ = frame_id;
463 video_header->frame_type = VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey;
464 } else {
465 video_header->frame_type = VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameDelta;
466 }
467 return kHasGenericDescriptor;
468 }
469
470 RtpGenericFrameDescriptor generic_frame_descriptor;
471 if (!rtp_packet.GetExtension<RtpGenericFrameDescriptorExtension00>(
472 &generic_frame_descriptor)) {
473 return kNoGenericDescriptor;
474 }
475
476 video_header->is_first_packet_in_frame =
477 generic_frame_descriptor.FirstPacketInSubFrame();
478 video_header->is_last_packet_in_frame =
479 generic_frame_descriptor.LastPacketInSubFrame();
480
481 if (generic_frame_descriptor.FirstPacketInSubFrame()) {
482 video_header->frame_type =
483 generic_frame_descriptor.FrameDependenciesDiffs().empty()
484 ? VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey
485 : VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameDelta;
486
487 auto& generic_descriptor_info = video_header->generic.emplace();
488 int64_t frame_id =
489 frame_id_unwrapper_.Unwrap(generic_frame_descriptor.FrameId());
490 generic_descriptor_info.frame_id = frame_id;
491 generic_descriptor_info.spatial_index =
492 generic_frame_descriptor.SpatialLayer();
493 generic_descriptor_info.temporal_index =
494 generic_frame_descriptor.TemporalLayer();
495 for (uint16_t fdiff : generic_frame_descriptor.FrameDependenciesDiffs()) {
496 generic_descriptor_info.dependencies.push_back(frame_id - fdiff);
497 }
498 }
499 video_header->width = generic_frame_descriptor.Width();
500 video_header->height = generic_frame_descriptor.Height();
501 return kHasGenericDescriptor;
502}
503
504void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::OnReceivedPayloadData(
505 rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer codec_payload,
506 const RtpPacketReceived& rtp_packet,
507 const RTPVideoHeader& video) {
508 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_task_checker_);
509
510 auto packet =
511 std::make_unique<video_coding::PacketBuffer::Packet>(rtp_packet, video);
512
513 RTPVideoHeader& video_header = packet->video_header;
514 video_header.rotation = kVideoRotation_0;
515 video_header.content_type = VideoContentType::UNSPECIFIED;
516 video_header.video_timing.flags = VideoSendTiming::kInvalid;
517 video_header.is_last_packet_in_frame |= rtp_packet.Marker();
518
519 if (const auto* vp9_header =
520 absl::get_if<RTPVideoHeaderVP9>(&video_header.video_type_header)) {
521 video_header.is_last_packet_in_frame |= vp9_header->end_of_frame;
522 video_header.is_first_packet_in_frame |= vp9_header->beginning_of_frame;
523 }
524
525 rtp_packet.GetExtension<VideoOrientation>(&video_header.rotation);
526 rtp_packet.GetExtension<VideoContentTypeExtension>(
527 &video_header.content_type);
528 rtp_packet.GetExtension<VideoTimingExtension>(&video_header.video_timing);
529 if (forced_playout_delay_max_ms_ && forced_playout_delay_min_ms_) {
530 video_header.playout_delay.max_ms = *forced_playout_delay_max_ms_;
531 video_header.playout_delay.min_ms = *forced_playout_delay_min_ms_;
532 } else {
533 rtp_packet.GetExtension<PlayoutDelayLimits>(&video_header.playout_delay);
534 }
535
536 ParseGenericDependenciesResult generic_descriptor_state =
537 ParseGenericDependenciesExtension(rtp_packet, &video_header);
538
539 if (!rtp_packet.recovered()) {
540 UpdatePacketReceiveTimestamps(
541 rtp_packet, video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey);
542 }
543
544 if (generic_descriptor_state == kDropPacket)
545 return;
546
547 // Color space should only be transmitted in the last packet of a frame,
548 // therefore, neglect it otherwise so that last_color_space_ is not reset by
549 // mistake.
550 if (video_header.is_last_packet_in_frame) {
551 video_header.color_space = rtp_packet.GetExtension<ColorSpaceExtension>();
552 if (video_header.color_space ||
553 video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
554 // Store color space since it's only transmitted when changed or for key
555 // frames. Color space will be cleared if a key frame is transmitted
556 // without color space information.
557 last_color_space_ = video_header.color_space;
558 } else if (last_color_space_) {
559 video_header.color_space = last_color_space_;
560 }
561 }
562 video_header.video_frame_tracking_id =
563 rtp_packet.GetExtension<VideoFrameTrackingIdExtension>();
564
565 if (loss_notification_controller_) {
566 if (rtp_packet.recovered()) {
567 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10336): Implement support for reordering.
568 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
569 << "LossNotificationController does not support reordering.";
570 } else if (generic_descriptor_state == kNoGenericDescriptor) {
571 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "LossNotificationController requires generic "
572 "frame descriptor, but it is missing.";
573 } else {
574 if (video_header.is_first_packet_in_frame) {
575 RTC_DCHECK(video_header.generic);
576 LossNotificationController::FrameDetails frame;
577 frame.is_keyframe =
578 video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey;
579 frame.frame_id = video_header.generic->frame_id;
580 frame.frame_dependencies = video_header.generic->dependencies;
581 loss_notification_controller_->OnReceivedPacket(
582 rtp_packet.SequenceNumber(), &frame);
583 } else {
584 loss_notification_controller_->OnReceivedPacket(
585 rtp_packet.SequenceNumber(), nullptr);
586 }
587 }
588 }
589
590 if (nack_module_) {
591 const bool is_keyframe =
592 video_header.is_first_packet_in_frame &&
593 video_header.frame_type == VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey;
594
595 packet->times_nacked = nack_module_->OnReceivedPacket(
596 rtp_packet.SequenceNumber(), is_keyframe, rtp_packet.recovered());
597 } else {
598 packet->times_nacked = -1;
599 }
600
601 if (codec_payload.size() == 0) {
602 NotifyReceiverOfEmptyPacket(packet->seq_num);
603 rtcp_feedback_buffer_.SendBufferedRtcpFeedback();
604 return;
605 }
606
607 if (packet->codec() == kVideoCodecH264) {
608 // Only when we start to receive packets will we know what payload type
609 // that will be used. When we know the payload type insert the correct
610 // sps/pps into the tracker.
611 if (packet->payload_type != last_payload_type_) {
612 last_payload_type_ = packet->payload_type;
613 InsertSpsPpsIntoTracker(packet->payload_type);
614 }
615
616 video_coding::H264SpsPpsTracker::FixedBitstream fixed =
617 tracker_.CopyAndFixBitstream(
618 rtc::MakeArrayView(codec_payload.cdata(), codec_payload.size()),
619 &packet->video_header);
620
621 switch (fixed.action) {
622 case video_coding::H264SpsPpsTracker::kRequestKeyframe:
623 rtcp_feedback_buffer_.RequestKeyFrame();
624 rtcp_feedback_buffer_.SendBufferedRtcpFeedback();
625 ABSL_FALLTHROUGH_INTENDED;
626 case video_coding::H264SpsPpsTracker::kDrop:
627 return;
628 case video_coding::H264SpsPpsTracker::kInsert:
629 packet->video_payload = std::move(fixed.bitstream);
630 break;
631 }
632#ifndef DISABLE_H265
633 } else if (packet->codec() == kVideoCodecH265) {
634 video_coding::H265VpsSpsPpsTracker::FixedBitstream fixed =
635 h265_tracker_.CopyAndFixBitstream(
636 rtc::MakeArrayView(codec_payload.cdata(), codec_payload.size()),
637 &packet->video_header);
638 switch (fixed.action) {
639 case video_coding::H265VpsSpsPpsTracker::kRequestKeyframe:
640 rtcp_feedback_buffer_.RequestKeyFrame();
641 rtcp_feedback_buffer_.SendBufferedRtcpFeedback();
642 ABSL_FALLTHROUGH_INTENDED;
643 case video_coding::H265VpsSpsPpsTracker::kDrop:
644 return;
645 case video_coding::H265VpsSpsPpsTracker::kInsert:
646 packet->video_payload = std::move(fixed.bitstream);
647 break;
648 }
649#endif
650 } else {
651 packet->video_payload = std::move(codec_payload);
652 }
653
654 rtcp_feedback_buffer_.SendBufferedRtcpFeedback();
655 frame_counter_.Add(packet->timestamp);
656 video_coding::PacketBuffer::InsertResult insert_result;
657 {
658 MutexLock lock(&packet_buffer_lock_);
659 int64_t unwrapped_rtp_seq_num =
660 rtp_seq_num_unwrapper_.Unwrap(rtp_packet.SequenceNumber());
661 auto& packet_info =
662 packet_infos_
663 .emplace(
664 unwrapped_rtp_seq_num,
665 RtpPacketInfo(
666 rtp_packet.Ssrc(), rtp_packet.Csrcs(),
667 rtp_packet.Timestamp(),
668 /*audio_level=*/absl::nullopt,
669 rtp_packet.GetExtension<AbsoluteCaptureTimeExtension>(),
670 /*receive_time_ms=*/clock_->TimeInMilliseconds()))
671 .first->second;
672
673 // Try to extrapolate absolute capture time if it is missing.
674 packet_info.set_absolute_capture_time(
675 absolute_capture_time_receiver_.OnReceivePacket(
676 AbsoluteCaptureTimeReceiver::GetSource(packet_info.ssrc(),
677 packet_info.csrcs()),
678 packet_info.rtp_timestamp(),
679 // Assume frequency is the same one for all video frames.
680 kVideoPayloadTypeFrequency, packet_info.absolute_capture_time()));
681
682 insert_result = packet_buffer_.InsertPacket(std::move(packet));
683 }
684 OnInsertedPacket(std::move(insert_result));
685}
686
687void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::OnRecoveredPacket(const uint8_t* rtp_packet,
688 size_t rtp_packet_length) {
689 RtpPacketReceived packet;
690 if (!packet.Parse(rtp_packet, rtp_packet_length))
691 return;
692 if (packet.PayloadType() == config_.rtp.red_payload_type) {
693 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Discarding recovered packet with RED encapsulation";
694 return;
695 }
696
697 packet.IdentifyExtensions(rtp_header_extensions_);
698 packet.set_payload_type_frequency(kVideoPayloadTypeFrequency);
699 // TODO(nisse): UlpfecReceiverImpl::ProcessReceivedFec passes both
700 // original (decapsulated) media packets and recovered packets to
701 // this callback. We need a way to distinguish, for setting
702 // packet.recovered() correctly. Ideally, move RED decapsulation out
703 // of the Ulpfec implementation.
704
705 ReceivePacket(packet);
706}
707
708// This method handles both regular RTP packets and packets recovered
709// via FlexFEC.
710void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::OnRtpPacket(const RtpPacketReceived& packet) {
711 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_task_checker_);
712
713 if (!receiving_) {
714 return;
715 }
716
717 ReceivePacket(packet);
718
719 // Update receive statistics after ReceivePacket.
720 // Receive statistics will be reset if the payload type changes (make sure
721 // that the first packet is included in the stats).
722 if (!packet.recovered()) {
723 rtp_receive_statistics_->OnRtpPacket(packet);
724 }
725
726 for (RtpPacketSinkInterface* secondary_sink : secondary_sinks_) {
727 secondary_sink->OnRtpPacket(packet);
728 }
729}

735 if (keyframe_request_sender_) {
736 keyframe_request_sender_->RequestKeyFrame();

738 rtp_rtcp_->SendPictureLossIndication();

768
769void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::OnInsertedPacket(
770 video_coding::PacketBuffer::InsertResult result) {
771 std::vector<std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject>> assembled_frames;
772 {
773 MutexLock lock(&packet_buffer_lock_);
774 video_coding::PacketBuffer::Packet* first_packet = nullptr;
775 int max_nack_count;
776 int64_t min_recv_time;
777 int64_t max_recv_time;
778 std::vector<rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t>> payloads;
779 RtpPacketInfos::vector_type packet_infos;
780
781 bool frame_boundary = true;
782 for (auto& packet : result.packets) {
783 // PacketBuffer promisses frame boundaries are correctly set on each
784 // packet. Document that assumption with the DCHECKs.
785 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(frame_boundary, packet->is_first_packet_in_frame());
786 int64_t unwrapped_rtp_seq_num =
787 rtp_seq_num_unwrapper_.Unwrap(packet->seq_num);
788 RTC_DCHECK(packet_infos_.count(unwrapped_rtp_seq_num) > 0);
789 RtpPacketInfo& packet_info = packet_infos_[unwrapped_rtp_seq_num];
790 if (packet->is_first_packet_in_frame()) {
791 first_packet = packet.get();
792 max_nack_count = packet->times_nacked;
793 min_recv_time = packet_info.receive_time().ms();
794 max_recv_time = packet_info.receive_time().ms();
795 payloads.clear();
796 packet_infos.clear();
797 } else {
798 max_nack_count = std::max(max_nack_count, packet->times_nacked);
799 min_recv_time =
800 std::min(min_recv_time, packet_info.receive_time().ms());
801 max_recv_time =
802 std::max(max_recv_time, packet_info.receive_time().ms());
803 }
804 payloads.emplace_back(packet->video_payload);
805 packet_infos.push_back(packet_info);
806
807 frame_boundary = packet->is_last_packet_in_frame();
808 if (packet->is_last_packet_in_frame()) {
809 auto depacketizer_it =
810 payload_type_map_.find(first_packet->payload_type);
811 RTC_CHECK(depacketizer_it != payload_type_map_.end());
812
813 rtc::scoped_refptr<EncodedImageBuffer> bitstream =
814 depacketizer_it->second->AssembleFrame(payloads);
815 if (!bitstream) {
816 // Failed to assemble a frame. Discard and continue.
817 continue;
818 }
819
820 const video_coding::PacketBuffer::Packet& last_packet = *packet;
821 assembled_frames.push_back(std::make_unique<RtpFrameObject>(
822 first_packet->seq_num, //
823 last_packet.seq_num, //
824 last_packet.marker_bit, //
825 max_nack_count, //
826 min_recv_time, //
827 max_recv_time, //
828 first_packet->timestamp, //
829 ntp_estimator_.Estimate(first_packet->timestamp), //
830 last_packet.video_header.video_timing, //
831 first_packet->payload_type, //
832 first_packet->codec(), //
833 last_packet.video_header.rotation, //
834 last_packet.video_header.content_type, //
835 first_packet->video_header, //
836 last_packet.video_header.color_space, //
837 RtpPacketInfos(std::move(packet_infos)), //
838 std::move(bitstream)));
839 }
840 }
841 RTC_DCHECK(frame_boundary);
842
843 if (result.buffer_cleared) {
844 packet_infos_.clear();
845 }
846 } // packet_buffer_lock_
847
848 if (result.buffer_cleared) {
849 {
850 MutexLock lock(&sync_info_lock_);
851 last_received_rtp_system_time_.reset();
852 last_received_keyframe_rtp_system_time_.reset();
853 last_received_keyframe_rtp_timestamp_.reset();
854 }
855 RequestKeyFrame();
856 }
857
858 for (auto& frame : assembled_frames) {
859 OnAssembledFrame(std::move(frame));
860 }
861}
862
863void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::OnAssembledFrame(
864 std::unique_ptr<RtpFrameObject> frame) {
865 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&network_tc_);
866 RTC_DCHECK(frame);
867
868#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
869 static const unsigned MaxFrameDelayCount = 3;
870 static const unsigned TimeStampQueueDurationInMs = 2000;
871 static const unsigned OneSecondInMs = 1000;
872 // FIXME: Consider using MovingAverage instead.
873 ++frameCount_;
874
875 auto frameTime = clock_->TimeInMilliseconds();
876 auto lastFrameTime = observedFrameTimeStamps_.empty() ? frameTime : observedFrameTimeStamps_.back();
877
878 if (observedFrameRate_) {
879 auto delay = frameTime - lastFrameTime;
880 if (delay > (MaxFrameDelayCount * OneSecondInMs / observedFrameRate_)) {
881 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "RtpVideoStreamReceiver::OnAssembledFrame at " << frameTime << ", previous frame was at " << lastFrameTime << ", observed frame rate is " << observedFrameRate_ << ", delay since last frame is " << (frameTime - lastFrameTime) << " ms, frame count is " << frameCount_ << ", size is " << frame->EncodedImage().size() << ", frame reception duration is " << (frame->video_timing().receive_finish_ms - frame->video_timing().receive_start_ms) << " ms, " << " observed samples count is " << observedFrameTimeStamps_.size() << ", observed samples duration is " << (observedFrameTimeStamps_.back() - observedFrameTimeStamps_.front());
882 }
883 }
884
885 observedFrameTimeStamps_.push_back(frameTime);
886 while (observedFrameTimeStamps_.front() <= (frameTime - TimeStampQueueDurationInMs))
887 observedFrameTimeStamps_.pop_front();
888
889 auto queueDuration = frameTime - observedFrameTimeStamps_.front();
890 if (queueDuration > OneSecondInMs)
891 observedFrameRate_ = observedFrameTimeStamps_.size() * OneSecondInMs / queueDuration;
892#endif
893
894 const absl::optional<RTPVideoHeader::GenericDescriptorInfo>& descriptor =
895 frame->GetRtpVideoHeader().generic;
896
897 if (loss_notification_controller_ && descriptor) {
898 loss_notification_controller_->OnAssembledFrame(
899 frame->first_seq_num(), descriptor->frame_id,
900 absl::c_linear_search(descriptor->decode_target_indications,
901 DecodeTargetIndication::kDiscardable),
902 descriptor->dependencies);
903 }
904
905 // If frames arrive before a key frame, they would not be decodable.
906 // In that case, request a key frame ASAP.
907 if (!has_received_frame_) {
908 if (frame->FrameType() != VideoFrameType::kVideoFrameKey) {
909 // |loss_notification_controller_|, if present, would have already
910 // requested a key frame when the first packet for the non-key frame
911 // had arrived, so no need to replicate the request.
912 if (!loss_notification_controller_) {
913 RequestKeyFrame();
914 }
915 }
916 has_received_frame_ = true;
917 }
918
919 MutexLock lock(&reference_finder_lock_);
920 // Reset |reference_finder_| if |frame| is new and the codec have changed.
921 if (current_codec_) {
922 bool frame_is_newer =
923 AheadOf(frame->Timestamp(), last_assembled_frame_rtp_timestamp_);
924
925 if (frame->codec_type() != current_codec_) {
926 if (frame_is_newer) {
927 // When we reset the |reference_finder_| we don't want new picture ids
928 // to overlap with old picture ids. To ensure that doesn't happen we
929 // start from the |last_completed_picture_id_| and add an offset in
930 // case of reordering.
931 reference_finder_ = std::make_unique<RtpFrameReferenceFinder>(
932 this,
933 last_completed_picture_id_ + std::numeric_limits<uint16_t>::max());
934 current_codec_ = frame->codec_type();
935 } else {
936 // Old frame from before the codec switch, discard it.
937 return;
938 }
939 }
940
941 if (frame_is_newer) {
942 last_assembled_frame_rtp_timestamp_ = frame->Timestamp();
943 }
944 } else {
945 current_codec_ = frame->codec_type();
946 last_assembled_frame_rtp_timestamp_ = frame->Timestamp();
947 }
948
949 if (buffered_frame_decryptor_ != nullptr) {
950 buffered_frame_decryptor_->ManageEncryptedFrame(std::move(frame));
951 } else if (frame_transformer_delegate_) {
952 frame_transformer_delegate_->TransformFrame(std::move(frame));
953 } else {
954 reference_finder_->ManageFrame(std::move(frame));
955 }
956}
957
958void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::OnCompleteFrame(
959 std::unique_ptr<EncodedFrame> frame) {
960 {
961 MutexLock lock(&last_seq_num_mutex_);
962 RtpFrameObject* rtp_frame = static_cast<RtpFrameObject*>(frame.get());
963 last_seq_num_for_pic_id_[rtp_frame->Id()] = rtp_frame->last_seq_num();
964 }
965 last_completed_picture_id_ =
966 std::max(last_completed_picture_id_, frame->Id());
967 complete_frame_callback_->OnCompleteFrame(std::move(frame));
968}

973 reference_finder_->ManageFrame(std::move(frame));

1026void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::AddSecondarySink(RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink) {
1027 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_task_checker_);
1028 RTC_DCHECK(!absl::c_linear_search(secondary_sinks_, sink));
1029 secondary_sinks_.push_back(sink);
1030}
1031
1032void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::RemoveSecondarySink(
1033 const RtpPacketSinkInterface* sink) {
1034 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_task_checker_);
1035 auto it = absl::c_find(secondary_sinks_, sink);
1036 if (it == secondary_sinks_.end()) {
1037 // We might be rolling-back a call whose setup failed mid-way. In such a
1038 // case, it's simpler to remove "everything" rather than remember what
1039 // has already been added.
1040 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Removal of unknown sink.";
1041 return;
1042 }
1043 secondary_sinks_.erase(it);
1044}

1051
1052void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::ReceivePacket(const RtpPacketReceived& packet) {
1053 if (packet.payload_size() == 0) {
1054 // Padding or keep-alive packet.
1055 // TODO(nisse): Could drop empty packets earlier, but need to figure out how
1056 // they should be counted in stats.
1057 NotifyReceiverOfEmptyPacket(packet.SequenceNumber());
1058 return;
1059 }
1060 if (packet.PayloadType() == config_.rtp.red_payload_type) {
1061 ParseAndHandleEncapsulatingHeader(packet);
1062 return;
1063 }
1064
1065 const auto type_it = payload_type_map_.find(packet.PayloadType());
1066 if (type_it == payload_type_map_.end()) {
1067 return;
1068 }
1069 absl::optional<VideoRtpDepacketizer::ParsedRtpPayload> parsed_payload =
1070 type_it->second->Parse(packet.PayloadBuffer());
1071 if (parsed_payload == absl::nullopt) {
1072 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed parsing payload.";
1073 return;
1074 }
1075
1076 OnReceivedPayloadData(std::move(parsed_payload->video_payload), packet,
1077 parsed_payload->video_header);
1078}
1079
1080void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::ParseAndHandleEncapsulatingHeader(
1081 const RtpPacketReceived& packet) {
1082 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_task_checker_);
1083 if (packet.PayloadType() == config_.rtp.red_payload_type &&
1084 packet.payload_size() > 0) {
1085 if (packet.payload()[0] == config_.rtp.ulpfec_payload_type) {
1086 // Notify video_receiver about received FEC packets to avoid NACKing these
1087 // packets.
1088 NotifyReceiverOfEmptyPacket(packet.SequenceNumber());
1089 }
1090 if (!ulpfec_receiver_->AddReceivedRedPacket(
1091 packet, config_.rtp.ulpfec_payload_type)) {
1092 return;
1093 }
1094 ulpfec_receiver_->ProcessReceivedFec();
1095 }
1096}
1097
1098// In the case of a video stream without picture ids and no rtx the
1099// RtpFrameReferenceFinder will need to know about padding to
1100// correctly calculate frame references.
1101void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::NotifyReceiverOfEmptyPacket(uint16_t seq_num) {
1102 {
1103 MutexLock lock(&reference_finder_lock_);
1104 reference_finder_->PaddingReceived(seq_num);
1105 }
1106
1107 video_coding::PacketBuffer::InsertResult insert_result;
1108 {
1109 MutexLock lock(&packet_buffer_lock_);
1110 insert_result = packet_buffer_.InsertPadding(seq_num);
1111 }
1112 OnInsertedPacket(std::move(insert_result));
1113
1114 if (nack_module_) {
1115 nack_module_->OnReceivedPacket(seq_num, /* is_keyframe = */ false,
1116 /* is _recovered = */ false);
1117 }
1118 if (loss_notification_controller_) {
1119 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10336): Handle empty packets.
1120 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1121 << "LossNotificationController does not expect empty packets.";
1122 }
1123}
1124
1125bool RtpVideoStreamReceiver::DeliverRtcp(const uint8_t* rtcp_packet,
1126 size_t rtcp_packet_length) {
1127 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&worker_task_checker_);
1128
1129 if (!receiving_) {
1130 return false;
1131 }
1132
1133 rtp_rtcp_->IncomingRtcpPacket(rtcp_packet, rtcp_packet_length);
1134
1135 int64_t rtt = 0;
1136 rtp_rtcp_->RTT(config_.rtp.remote_ssrc, &rtt, nullptr, nullptr, nullptr);
1137 if (rtt == 0) {
1138 // Waiting for valid rtt.
1139 return true;
1140 }
1141 uint32_t ntp_secs = 0;
1142 uint32_t ntp_frac = 0;
1143 uint32_t rtp_timestamp = 0;
1144 uint32_t recieved_ntp_secs = 0;
1145 uint32_t recieved_ntp_frac = 0;
1146 if (rtp_rtcp_->RemoteNTP(&ntp_secs, &ntp_frac, &recieved_ntp_secs,
1147 &recieved_ntp_frac, &rtp_timestamp) != 0) {
1148 // Waiting for RTCP.
1149 return true;
1150 }
1151 NtpTime recieved_ntp(recieved_ntp_secs, recieved_ntp_frac);
1152 int64_t time_since_recieved =
1153 clock_->CurrentNtpInMilliseconds() - recieved_ntp.ToMs();
1154 // Don't use old SRs to estimate time.
1155 if (time_since_recieved <= 1) {
1156 ntp_estimator_.UpdateRtcpTimestamp(rtt, ntp_secs, ntp_frac, rtp_timestamp);
1157 absl::optional<int64_t> remote_to_local_clock_offset_ms =
1158 ntp_estimator_.EstimateRemoteToLocalClockOffsetMs();
1159 if (remote_to_local_clock_offset_ms.has_value()) {
1160 absolute_capture_time_receiver_.SetRemoteToLocalClockOffset(
1161 Int64MsToQ32x32(*remote_to_local_clock_offset_ms));
1162 }
1163 }
1164
1165 return true;
1166}
1167
1168void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::FrameContinuous(int64_t picture_id) {
1169 if (!nack_module_)
1170 return;
1171
1172 int seq_num = -1;
1173 {
1174 MutexLock lock(&last_seq_num_mutex_);
1175 auto seq_num_it = last_seq_num_for_pic_id_.find(picture_id);
1176 if (seq_num_it != last_seq_num_for_pic_id_.end())
1177 seq_num = seq_num_it->second;
1178 }
1179 if (seq_num != -1)
1180 nack_module_->ClearUpTo(seq_num);
1181}
1182
1183void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::FrameDecoded(int64_t picture_id) {
1184 int seq_num = -1;
1185 {
1186 MutexLock lock(&last_seq_num_mutex_);
1187 auto seq_num_it = last_seq_num_for_pic_id_.find(picture_id);
1188 if (seq_num_it != last_seq_num_for_pic_id_.end()) {
1189 seq_num = seq_num_it->second;
1190 last_seq_num_for_pic_id_.erase(last_seq_num_for_pic_id_.begin(),
1191 ++seq_num_it);
1192 }
1193 }
1194 if (seq_num != -1) {
1195 {
1196 MutexLock lock(&packet_buffer_lock_);
1197 packet_buffer_.ClearTo(seq_num);
1198 int64_t unwrapped_rtp_seq_num = rtp_seq_num_unwrapper_.Unwrap(seq_num);
1199 packet_infos_.erase(packet_infos_.begin(),
1200 packet_infos_.upper_bound(unwrapped_rtp_seq_num));
1201 }
1202 MutexLock lock(&reference_finder_lock_);
1203 reference_finder_->ClearTo(seq_num);
1204 }
1205}

1208 rtp_rtcp_->SetRTCPStatus(state == kNetworkUp ? config_.rtp.rtcp_mode
1209 : RtcpMode::kOff);

1222void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::UpdateHistograms() {
1223 FecPacketCounter counter = ulpfec_receiver_->GetPacketCounter();
1224 if (counter.first_packet_time_ms == -1)
1225 return;
1226
1227 int64_t elapsed_sec =
1228 (clock_->TimeInMilliseconds() - counter.first_packet_time_ms) / 1000;
1229 if (elapsed_sec < metrics::kMinRunTimeInSeconds)
1230 return;
1231
1232 if (counter.num_packets > 0) {
1233 RTC_HISTOGRAM_PERCENTAGE(
1234 "WebRTC.Video.ReceivedFecPacketsInPercent",
1235 static_cast<int>(counter.num_fec_packets * 100 / counter.num_packets));
1236 }
1237 if (counter.num_fec_packets > 0) {
1238 RTC_HISTOGRAM_PERCENTAGE("WebRTC.Video.RecoveredMediaPacketsInPercentOfFec",
1239 static_cast<int>(counter.num_recovered_packets *
1240 100 / counter.num_fec_packets));
1241 }
1242 if (config_.rtp.ulpfec_payload_type != -1) {
1243 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_10000(
1244 "WebRTC.Video.FecBitrateReceivedInKbps",
1245 static_cast<int>(counter.num_bytes * 8 / elapsed_sec / 1000));
1246 }
1247}

1249void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::InsertSpsPpsIntoTracker(uint8_t payload_type) {
1250 auto codec_params_it = pt_codec_params_.find(payload_type);
1251 if (codec_params_it == pt_codec_params_.end())
1252 return;
1253
1254 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Found out of band supplied codec parameters for"
1255 " payload type: "
1256 << static_cast<int>(payload_type);
1257
1258 H264SpropParameterSets sprop_decoder;
1259 auto sprop_base64_it =
1260 codec_params_it->second.find(cricket::kH264FmtpSpropParameterSets);
1261
1262 if (sprop_base64_it == codec_params_it->second.end())
1263 return;
1264
1265 if (!sprop_decoder.DecodeSprop(sprop_base64_it->second.c_str()))
1266 return;
1267
1268 tracker_.InsertSpsPpsNalus(sprop_decoder.sps_nalu(),
1269 sprop_decoder.pps_nalu());
1270}
1271
1272void RtpVideoStreamReceiver::UpdatePacketReceiveTimestamps(
1273 const RtpPacketReceived& packet,
1274 bool is_keyframe) {
1275 Timestamp now = clock_->CurrentTime();
1276 {
1277 MutexLock lock(&sync_info_lock_);
1278 if (is_keyframe ||
1279 last_received_keyframe_rtp_timestamp_ == packet.Timestamp()) {
1280 last_received_keyframe_rtp_timestamp_ = packet.Timestamp();
1281 last_received_keyframe_rtp_system_time_ = now;
1282 }
1283 last_received_rtp_system_time_ = now;
1284 last_received_rtp_timestamp_ = packet.Timestamp();
1285 }
1286
1287 // Periodically log the RTP header of incoming packets.
1288 if (now.ms() - last_packet_log_ms_ > kPacketLogIntervalMs) {
1289 rtc::StringBuilder ss;
1290 ss << "Packet received on SSRC: " << packet.Ssrc()
1291 << " with payload type: " << static_cast<int>(packet.PayloadType())
1292 << ", timestamp: " << packet.Timestamp()
1293 << ", sequence number: " << packet.SequenceNumber()
1294 << ", arrival time: " << ToString(packet.arrival_time());
1295 int32_t time_offset;
1296 if (packet.GetExtension<TransmissionOffset>(&time_offset)) {
1297 ss << ", toffset: " << time_offset;
1298 }
1299 uint32_t send_time;
1300 if (packet.GetExtension<AbsoluteSendTime>(&send_time)) {
1301 ss << ", abs send time: " << send_time;
1302 }
1303 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ss.str();
1304 last_packet_log_ms_ = now.ms();
1305 }
1306}
